<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFF8FFC7FF71FA19FC08F983" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF8FFC7FF71FA19FD74FA4B" blockId="16.[151,1436,1446,1582]" box="[151,649,1483,1509]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFF8FFC7FF79FA19FF14FA4B" box="[159,233,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="62.[151,250,1923,1947]" captionTargetBox="[217,1371,196,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-32@62.[206,1381,181,1899]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 9. Eudocima materna group and African Eudocima adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605516/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs 9</figureCitation>
: G–H, 19: D, 24: M–Q, 31: B, 92: F)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF8FFC7FF71FA3DFC08F983" blockId="16.[151,1436,1446,1582]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
This large sexually dimorphic species is separated from 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FCE8FA3DFC86F9A7" baseAuthorityName="Saalmuller" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[782,891,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boseae">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FCE8FA3DFC86F9A7" box="[782,891,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">E. boseae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and all other 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FBF3FA3DFB22F9A7" box="[1045,1247,1519,1545]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FBF3FA3DFB7AF9A7" box="[1045,1159,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Eudocima</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
as described un- der 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FF24F9C1FED2F983" baseAuthorityName="Saalmuller" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[194,303,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boseae">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FF24F9C1FED2F983" box="[194,303,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">E. boseae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(above). It is a 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFF8FFC7FE39F9C1FD9BF983" box="[479,614,1555,1581]" name="Madagascar" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
endemic sympatric with 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FC67F9C1FC08F983" box="[897,1013,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FC67F9C1FC0CF983" baseAuthorityName="Saalmuller" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[897,1009,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boseae">E. boseae</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
